The Telegraph - Calcutta
 7 from Bangla for finals
 A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Seven from Bangladesh are among the nearly 270 participants in fray for the finals of the 17th The Telegraph Schools Chess Championship which begins on Friday. The meet, which will be held in the 11-round Swiss league format, will conclude on August 30. The inauguration will also take place on Friday when Grandmaster and a product of the tournament, Surya Sekhar Ganguly, will respond to a move, to be made by the youngest participant. At a press conference on Thursday evening, Asoke Ghosh, president of the Alekhine Chess Club, the organisers, informed that the champion will be richer by Rs 15,000. The runners-up will receive Rs 10,000 and Rs 7,000 for the third-finisher. The total cash prize is Rs 60,000. Four visually challenged players will also be seen in action. Suvrodip Das, at four years and seven months, of Gurukul Vidyamandir is the youngest boy, and five-year-old Chandreyee Hazra of Gospel Home School the youngest girl. The top-five from the Guwahati, Bhubaneswar and Jamshedpur legs are also in fray. THE RATED PLAYERS 1. Purushothaman T. (AP), Elo rating 2171. 2. Debayan Majumdar (Bengal), 2161. 3. Rajib Dhar (Assam), 2135. 4. Minhazuddin Ahmed Sagar (Bangladesh), 2113. 5. Mohammed Imran Ali (Bangladesh), 2111. 6. Lalith Babu M.R. (AP), 2104. 7. Mahendra Venkat L. (AP), 2098. 8. Soumya Thakurta (WB), 2094. 9. Debaditta Sinha Biswas (Bengal), 2072. 10. Parag Hunney (Chattisgarh), 2060.  Copyright 
